<br>
It began as a joke between a few smiths on the server: Your faction with Coalition of Morell-Thule Tradesfolk decreased! However, the more some of us talked about it, the more it occurred to us that it might actually be a good idea: a Coalition of working masters and grandmasters of the various trades on Morell-Thule.<br>
<br>
Why, we could negotiate bulk discounts! We could practice price collusion like dirty corporate platinum grubbers! We could develop mechanisms to promote and sell our wares by finding ways to work together instead of duplicating each other's efforts.<br>
<br>
Well, after a bunch of, &quot;Yeah, that would be a good idea&quot; tell-fests, it's time for us to start discussing these matters more seriously. If you are a master/grandmaster tradesperson on Morell-Thule that is actively involved in making and selling wares (rather than, for example, having practiced the skill just to complete Velious quests), then I would appreciate your thoughts on the formation of a Coalition of Morell-Thule Tradesfolk at this new ezboard:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub48.ezboard.com/bcoalitionofmorellthuletradesfolk">pub48.ezboard.com/bcoalit...tradesfolk</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
